# Title: Chirping Crickets - Floating Lights Down the River
Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.00,0:00:03.70,Sora OP,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(0,3600)\bord2.25\3c&H1F1F1F&\be6\c&HFFFFFC&}so ra no wo to
Dialogue: 0,0:00:03.85,0:00:13.52,Sora OP,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be1\fad(200,200)\3c&H141414&}The brilliant glow of this sky, does it carry right into your heart?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:13.83,0:00:22.91,Sora OP,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be1\fad(200,1600)\3c&H141414&}The melody you heard in your dream, it plays like the silence
Dialogue: 0,0:00:23.53,0:00:28.12,Sora OP,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be1\fad(200,200)\3c&H141414&}Even if your hands are still far from that dream,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:28.12,0:00:33.34,Sora OP,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be1\fad(200,200)\3c&H141414&}Come now and remember that kindly voice
Dialogue: 0,0:00:33.34,0:00:46.28,Sora OP,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be1\fad(50,200)\3c&H141414&}Someone was there singing for you, the happiness they sang about
Dialogue: 0,0:00:46.28,0:00:55.68,Sora OP,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be1\fad(200,200)\3c&H141414&}Sound of the sky, echo on high, break through that overwhelming sadness
Dialogue: 0,0:00:55.68,0:01:00.62,Sora OP,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be1\fad(200,200)\3c&H141414&}Everything that shines in your eyes
Dialogue: 0,0:01:00.62,0:01:06.08,Sora OP,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be1\fad(200,400)\3c&H141414&}Is part of the real world
Dialogue: 0,0:01:06.34,0:01:15.55,Sora OP,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be1\fad(100,200)\3c&H141414&}Even your tears can't leave you here to stay forever
Dialogue: 0,0:01:15.71,0:01:27.51,Sora OP,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be1\fad(200,4000)\3c&H141414&}In this gentle light pouring down onto you, play tomorrow's song
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.56,0:04:17.57,Sora OP,,0000,0000,0000,,{\bord0\c&HFFFFFF&\1a&00&}Chirping Crickets - Floating Lights on the River
Dialogue: 0,0:22:40.40,0:22:46.47,Sora ED,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(100,100)}Love and friendship - put these feelings together
Dialogue: 0,0:22:46.47,0:22:49.26,Sora ED,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(100,200)}And sing of how important they are
Dialogue: 0,0:23:04.61,0:23:07.74,Sora ED,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(100,100)}I was so happy that I cried
Dialogue: 0,0:23:10.58,0:23:13.71,Sora ED,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(100,100)}It hurt so bad that I laughed
Dialogue: 0,0:23:15.54,0:23:22.55,Sora ED,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(100,100)}But that all just goes to show that I'm alive
Dialogue: 0,0:23:22.55,0:23:26.68,Sora ED,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(100,800)}Let's just walk it slowly
Dialogue: 0,0:23:26.68,0:23:28.37,Sora ED,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(100,100)\3c&HE5A9EA&}Everybody singing!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:28.37,0:23:32.66,Sora ED,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(100,100)}Just tell me a bit of what you think
Dialogue: 0,0:23:32.66,0:23:33.98,Sora ED,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(100,100)\3c&HE5A9EA&}You're just my friend!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:33.98,0:23:39.99,Sora ED,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(100,100)}Love and friendship - even though they might waver
Dialogue: 1,0:23:37.02,0:23:39.99,Sora ED,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(100,100)\3c&HE5A9EA&\an8}I know, you know, little happy
Dialogue: 0,0:23:39.99,0:23:45.82,Sora ED,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(100,100)}I want us to echo on forever
Dialogue: 0,0:23:42.73,0:23:45.82,Sora ED,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(100,100)\3c&HE5A9EA&\an8}Can you hear my precious note?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:45.82,0:23:52.20,Sora ED,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(100,100)}All these words that there are can't even describe it
Dialogue: 0,0:23:52.20,0:23:57.95,Sora ED,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(100,1400)}Our harmony
Dialogue: 0,0:23:57.95,0:24:02.59,Sora ED,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(100,1400)}Can you hear it? Our harmony
Dialogue: 0,0:01:35.17,0:01:38.09,SoraDefault,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you ready, my little ones?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:38.91,0:01:40.38,SoraDefault,,0000,0000,0000,,Standby to advance!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:40.38,0:01:40.99,SoraDefault,,0000,0000,0000,,Forward!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:40.99,0:01:42.29,SoraDefault,,0000,0000,0000,,Advancing!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:44.71,0:01:46.04,SoraDefault,,0000,0000,0000,,Where are our reinforcements?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:46.61,0:01:49.29,SoraDefault,,0000,0000,0000,,Left, forty degrees! Main armament, standby!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:52.92,0:01:54.05,SoraDefault,,0000,0000,0000,,Distance, 400.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:54.05,0:01:56.88,SoraDefault,,0000,0000,0000,,Load shell. Incendiary round.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:56.88,0:01:58.16,SoraDefault,,0000,0000,0000,,Check.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:58.93,0:01:59.87,SoraDefault,,0000,0000,0000,,Olga!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:59.87,0:02:01.09,SoraDefault,,0000,0000,0000,,Leave it to me!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:01.09,0:02:05.10,SoraDefault,,0000,0000,0000,,I've been canned in this thing for three days! I'm not dying until I get a shower!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:06.57,0:02:07.73,SoraDefault,,0000,0000,0000,,Target locked!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:07.73,0:02:08.48,SoraDefault,,0000,0000,0000,,Fire!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:16.94,0:02:18.06,SoraDefault,,0000,0000,0000,,Direct hit!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:18.06,0:02:20.22,SoraDefault,,0000,0000,0000,,Anna, signal the forces to our rear.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:20.22,0:02:23.38,SoraDefault,,0000,0000,0000,,Have destroyed enemy unit. Take up our rear.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:23.38,0:02:24.17,SoraDefault,,0000,0000,0000,,Roger!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:24.17,0:02:26.41,SoraDefault,,0000,0000,0000,,Filicia, cover her.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:26.41,0:02:28.21,SoraDefault,,0000,0000,0000,,Y- Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:30.26,0:02:33.80,SoraDefault,,0000,0000,0000,,It's flashing out there, but there's no thunder. Just relax.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:33.80,0:02:35.67,SoraDefault,,0000,0000,0000,,I know!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:43.93,0:02:45.18,SoraDefault,,0000,0000,0000,,Three o'clock!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.93,0:03:13.80,SoraDefault,,0000,0000,0000,,No...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:17.77,0:03:18.76,SoraDefault,,0000,0000,0000,,Lieutenant Anna!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:32.81,0:03:38.69,SoraDefault,,0000,0000,0000,,Paper!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.69,0:03:45.34,SoraDefault,,0000,0000,0000,,Bamboo!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:19.57,0:04:21.11,SoraDefault,,0000,0000,0000,,Come on, Noël!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.11,0:04:24.07,SoraDefault,,0000,0000,0000,,It won't get clean if you don't scrub harder!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.09,0:04:47.10,SoraDefault,,0000,0000,0000,,It's so hot!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.28,0:04:54.68,SoraDefault,,0000,0000,0000,,This building gets way too cold in the winter, but thank God it's cool in the summer.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.68,0:04:58.22,SoraDefault,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh? Weren't Filicia and Rio in charge of the laundry today?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.22,0:05:01.53,SoraDefault,,0000,0000,0000,,They said they were busy so they asked us to do it for them.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.53,0:05:02.61,SoraDefault,,0000,0000,0000,,Whose is that?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.61,0:05:04.25,SoraDefault,,0000,0000,0000,,Filicia's.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.25,0:05:08.12,SoraDefault,,0000,0000,0000,,She said she wasn't hungry, so we could have them.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.95,0:05:12.37,SoraDefault,,0000,0000,0000,,Then this one's mine!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.92,0:05:17.08,SoraDefault,,0000,0000,0000,,What are you doing? Are you starting on dinner?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.08,0:05:21.88,SoraDefault,,0000,0000,0000,,Ouch. What are you making? You shouldn't play with your food.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.88,0:05:24.40,SoraDefault,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm not playing!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.40,0:05:26.25,SoraDefault,,0000,0000,0000,,It's almost time for {\i1}Obon{\i0}, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.25,0:05:29.02,SoraDefault,,0000,0000,0000,,What? What's this {\i1}Obon{\i0}?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.02,0:05:31.22,SoraDefault,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Fiesta des Lumières{\i0}.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.68,0:05:32.72,SoraDefault,,0000,0000,0000,,Fi?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.72,0:05:37.60,SoraDefault,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Fiesta des Lumières{\i0} is an event specific to the southern part of Helvetia.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.60,0:05:39.36,SoraDefault,,0000,0000,0000,,It originated in a local belief that
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.36,0:05:43.99,SoraDefault,,0000,0000,0000,,for a short period during the summer, the souls of the dead would return to the world of the living.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.99,0:05:48.87,SoraDefault,,0000,0000,0000,,Paper lanterns are floated down the river as a symbol of their return to the afterlife.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.87,0:05:53.87,SoraDefault,,0000,0000,0000,,In some regions, the festival is called {\i1}Obon{\i0}.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.87,0:05:55.12,SoraDefault,,0000,0000,0000,,Right. Here you are.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.12,0:05:56.67,SoraDefault,,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.70,0:06:02.29,SoraDefault,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh? So it's the same thing?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.29,0:06:04.86,SoraDefault,,0000,0000,0000,,Souls returning?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.86,0:06:08.96,SoraDefault,,0000,0000,0000,,Wait, wait! What does that mean? Does that mean ghosts come back?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.96,0:06:10.14,SoraDefault,,0000,0000,0000,,In one sense.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.14,0:06:14.30,SoraDefault,,0000,0000,0000,,Paper lanterns? That sounds so wonderful!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.30,0:06:16.68,SoraDefault,,0000,0000,0000,,We used to hold bonfires back in my village, but-
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.68,0:06:20.86,SoraDefault,,0000,0000,0000,,No! Dead people go to Heaven and stay there forever!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.86,0:06:23.57,SoraDefault,,0000,0000,0000,,Only the evil spirits wander around on earth!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.57,0:06:26.19,SoraDefault,,0000,0000,0000,,What? That's not true!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.19,0:06:28.04,SoraDefault,,0000,0000,0000,,But the Church...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.04,0:06:29.49,SoraDefault,,0000,0000,0000,,We're home!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.49,0:06:32.24,SoraDefault,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey! Mind lending us a hand?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.24,0:06:36.16,SoraDefault,,0000,0000,0000,,When did you two go shopping?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.16,0:06:38.04,SoraDefault,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, aren't those...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.04,0:06:40.38,SoraDefault,,0000,0000,0000,,They looked delicious, so we bought them.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.38,0:06:42.04,SoraDefault,,0000,0000,0000,,And these too.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.68,0:06:52.71,SoraDefault,,0000,0000,0000,,Is it like this?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.71,0:06:56.81,SoraDefault,,0000,0000,0000,,No, Father. I told you, it's like this.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.81,0:06:58.69,SoraDefault,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm done!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.95,0:07:01.94,SoraDefault,,0000,0000,0000,,Your mom and dad?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.94,0:07:05.69,SoraDefault,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, you did a really good job!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.69,0:07:09.59,SoraDefault,,0000,0000,0000,,What? Even the Church approves of it?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.59,0:07:11.45,SoraDefault,,0000,0000,0000,,That Fi-whatever?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.45,0:07:12.53,SoraDefault,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.53,0:07:15.21,SoraDefault,,0000,0000,0000,,The central diocese would start a riot,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.21,0:07:17.07,SoraDefault,,0000,0000,0000,,but this is the middle of nowhere.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.07,0:07:18.58,SoraDefault,,0000,0000,0000,,That's not much of a reason...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.84,0:07:27.16,SoraDefault,,0000,0000,0000,,In my village, we would make horses and cows out of cucumbers and eggplants for our ancestors to ride.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:28.62,0:07:34.26,SoraDefault,,0000,0000,0000,,And to console our ancestors, we would all dance together.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.72,0:07:38.75,SoraDefault,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you two making them too?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:38.75,0:07:42.08,SoraDefault,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah. Last year we only watched, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.63,0:07:58.86,SoraDefault,,0000,0000,0000,,Maintaining smooth cultural relations with the local residents is also part of our job.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.86,0:08:03.08,SoraDefault,,0000,0000,0000,,If you don't get into details, it's just another festival.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.42,0:08:05.46,SoraDefault,,0000,0000,0000,,Right, Filicia?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.98,0:09:13.99,SoraDefault,,0000,0000,0000,,{\c&H000000&\bord0\an3\pos(1840,1050)}Sound of the Sky
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.99,0:09:19.24,SoraDefault,,0000,0000,0000,,{\c&H000000&\bord0\an1\pos(80,1050)}Sound of the Sky
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.63,0:09:20.79,SoraDefault,,0000,0000,0000,,Filicia!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.80,0:09:30.55,SoraDefault,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you okay? Does it hurt?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.55,0:09:32.54,SoraDefault,,0000,0000,0000,,No, I'm fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.54,0:09:34.28,SoraDefault,,0000,0000,0000,,I just made a little mistake.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.28,0:09:37.93,SoraDefault,,0000,0000,0000,,But it's pretty rare for you to make a mistake like that, Commander.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.93,0:09:40.00,SoraDefault,,0000,0000,0000,,I mean, you're not Kanata.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:40.88,0:09:46.06,SoraDefault,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, it's been pretty hot these last few days.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.06,0:09:47.61,SoraDefault,,0000,0000,0000,,I haven't slept very well.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.40,0:09:50.77,SoraDefault,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll go get a little rest.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.07,0:09:59.01,SoraDefault,,0000,0000,0000,,Filicia...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.01,0:10:02.04,SoraDefault,,0000,0000,0000,,The Commander's acting a bit weird today.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.04,0:10:07.54,SoraDefault,,0000,0000,0000,,She didn't eat her lunch, and then she buys watermelons without checking our food budget?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.54,0:10:10.61,SoraDefault,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sure even she has her reasons.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.28,0:10:15.59,SoraDefault,,0000,0000,0000,,I think I'll talk to her...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.59,0:10:16.42,SoraDefault,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.26,0:10:21.14,SoraDefault,,0000,0000,0000,,Everyone has a part of themselves they don't want anyone to know about.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.14,0:10:22.93,SoraDefault,,0000,0000,0000,,Just leave her alone.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.02,0:10:27.50,SoraDefault,,0000,0000,0000,,Noël?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:28.19,0:10:30.30,SoraDefault,,0000,0000,0000,,Do you know what happened, Rio?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.30,0:10:31.79,SoraDefault,,0000,0000,0000,,I read the files.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.79,0:10:34.42,SoraDefault,,0000,0000,0000,,I was there when it happened.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.42,0:10:35.45,SoraDefault,,0000,0000,0000,,So...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.72,0:10:52.21,SoraDefault,,0000,0000,0000,,Filicia...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.90,0:11:00.97,SoraAlt,,0000,0000,0000,,Put your elbow into it. Good.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.11,0:11:05.07,SoraAlt,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(0,200)}There, there, now.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.98,0:11:12.48,SoraAlt,,0000,0000,0000,,And then a ghost that looked just like the Commander
Dialogue: 0,0:11:17.23,0:11:22.12,SoraDefault,,0000,0000,0000,,There used to be millions of things living in this ocean.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:22.12,0:11:24.30,SoraDefault,,0000,0000,0000,,It's hard to believe that now.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:25.59,0:11:27.40,SoraDefault,,0000,0000,0000,,Did anyone ever tell you?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.40,0:11:30.30,SoraDefault,,0000,0000,0000,,They say the world is slowly dying,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.30,0:11:34.63,SoraDefault,,0000,0000,0000,,and eventually, all humanity will fall completely into ruin.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.63,0:11:37.13,SoraDefault,,0000,0000,0000,,Those are just...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.13,0:11:38.51,SoraDefault,,0000,0000,0000,,people talking.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:38.51,0:11:42.29,SoraDefault,,0000,0000,0000,,But if it were true,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:42.29,0:11:46.12,SoraDefault,,0000,0000,0000,,then what are we fighting for?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:58.41,0:12:00.36,SoraDefault,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.36,0:12:02.73,SoraDefault,,0000,0000,0000,,still alive?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:37.53,0:12:39.54,SoraDefault,,0000,0000,0000,,Ideographs?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:43.88,0:12:46.20,SoraDefault,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:46.20,0:12:50.80,SoraDefault,,0000,0000,0000,,I wish I could read your final words.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.13,0:12:53.67,SoraDefault,,0000,0000,0000,,This equipment...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:55.42,0:12:57.88,SoraDefault,,0000,0000,0000,,Could you be a soldier from-
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.96,0:13:13.05,SoraDefault,,0000,0000,0000,,Commander...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:13.83,0:13:15.62,SoraDefault,,0000,0000,0000,,Lieutenant Olga...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.62,0:13:17.21,SoraDefault,,0000,0000,0000,,Marlina...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.21,0:13:18.72,SoraDefault,,0000,0000,0000,,Anna...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:19.69,0:13:21.41,SoraDefault,,0000,0000,0000,,Why
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.41,0:13:22.82,SoraDefault,,0000,0000,0000,,only me?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:25.40,0:13:26.34,SoraDefault,,0000,0000,0000,,Why
Dialogue: 0,0:13:27.81,0:13:29.57,SoraDefault,,0000,0000,0000,,are you crying?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.94,0:13:32.33,SoraDefault,,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:32.33,0:13:37.66,SoraDefault,,0000,0000,0000,,So there are still people alive in this world.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.58,0:13:39.96,SoraDefault,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:44.20,0:13:45.84,SoraDefault,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm truly sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.83,0:13:48.19,SoraDefault,,0000,0000,0000,,Why
Dialogue: 0,0:13:48.19,0:13:50.19,SoraDefault,,0000,0000,0000,,are you apologizing?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.19,0:13:51.92,SoraDefault,,0000,0000,0000,,Because...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:51.92,0:13:54.20,SoraDefault,,0000,0000,0000,,we lost.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.38,0:13:58.05,SoraDefault,,0000,0000,0000,,Against them.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:59.61,0:14:01.61,SoraDefault,,0000,0000,0000,,We couldn't protect you.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.61,0:14:03.79,SoraDefault,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm truly sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.32,0:14:25.90,SoraDefault,,0000,0000,0000,,The world is already dead.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.35,0:14:27.99,SoraDefault,,0000,0000,0000,,No...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:28.55,0:14:30.82,SoraDefault,,0000,0000,0000,,You are just the dregs.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:31.88,0:14:35.15,SoraDefault,,0000,0000,0000,,The last few bubbles in the bowl.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:35.86,0:14:37.81,SoraDefault,,0000,0000,0000,,Humanity...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.81,0:14:42.94,SoraDefault,,0000,0000,0000,,The world will never shine as it did before.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.94,0:14:45.28,SoraDefault,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't decide that for us!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.28,0:14:47.70,SoraDefault,,0000,0000,0000,,But that is the truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:48.58,0:14:51.35,SoraDefault,,0000,0000,0000,,So just end it.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:53.37,0:15:00.95,SoraDefault,,0000,0000,0000,,Living pathos in the dregs of the world, in this despair? It's far too desolate.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:00.95,0:15:02.46,SoraDefault,,0000,0000,0000,,No. I won't.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.46,0:15:04.30,SoraDefault,,0000,0000,0000,,Why not?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:04.30,0:15:08.35,SoraDefault,,0000,0000,0000,,Does remaining in this world have any meaning?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.28,0:15:10.93,SoraDefault,,0000,0000,0000,,There...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:33.87,0:15:35.25,SoraDefault,,0000,0000,0000,,Save me...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:42.33,0:15:45.25,SoraDefault,,0000,0000,0000,,I am here! I am alive!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:45.25,0:15:47.76,SoraDefault,,0000,0000,0000,,Please! Save me!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.61,0:16:11.11,SoraDefault,,0000,0000,0000,,You...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.12,0:16:15.64,SoraDefault,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:16.31,0:16:20.06,SoraDefault,,0000,0000,0000,,If only my corps had arrived half a day sooner,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.06,0:16:22.79,SoraDefault,,0000,0000,0000,,it wouldn't have turned out this way.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.70,0:16:26.04,SoraDefault,,0000,0000,0000,,Your Highness, Princess Iliya.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:32.27,0:16:34.30,SoraDefault,,0000,0000,0000,,But I was surprised.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:34.30,0:16:35.44,SoraDefault,,0000,0000,0000,,About what?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.44,0:16:40.31,SoraDefault,,0000,0000,0000,,You completely ignored the {\i1}Fiesta des Lumières{\i0} last year.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:40.31,0:16:43.12,SoraDefault,,0000,0000,0000,,Why the change of faith?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:43.12,0:16:44.81,SoraDefault,,0000,0000,0000,,Well...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:48.82,0:16:50.48,SoraDefault,,0000,0000,0000,,Isn't it a pretty color?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.48,0:16:54.41,SoraDefault,,0000,0000,0000,,Treize is famous for these. I bought them at the flea market.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:55.67,0:16:59.33,SoraDefault,,0000,0000,0000,,They're amazing! They're so wonderful!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.33,0:17:00.69,SoraDefault,,0000,0000,0000,,Aren't they?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:00.69,0:17:02.33,SoraDefault,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.23,0:17:04.98,SoraDefault,,0000,0000,0000,,I know.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:04.98,0:17:07.96,SoraDefault,,0000,0000,0000,,She used to mean everything to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:08.48,0:17:13.48,SoraDefault,,0000,0000,0000,,I thought I wanted to protect my country, my people, like she did.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.87,0:17:17.17,SoraDefault,,0000,0000,0000,,But sometimes, I think...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:17.93,0:17:20.70,SoraDefault,,0000,0000,0000,,Is there any meaning in it?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:24.46,0:17:27.36,SoraDefault,,0000,0000,0000,,So if she really did come back...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.36,0:17:29.86,SoraDefault,,0000,0000,0000,,I wanted her to tell me.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:32.66,0:17:34.76,SoraDefault,,0000,0000,0000,,But what about you?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:35.47,0:17:37.24,SoraDefault,,0000,0000,0000,,They're worried about you.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:38.10,0:17:42.28,SoraDefault,,0000,0000,0000,,You're right. I may have made them worry a little.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.28,0:17:43.81,SoraDefault,,0000,0000,0000,,I've failed as a Commander.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:43.81,0:17:45.78,SoraDefault,,0000,0000,0000,,They aren't the only ones!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:45.78,0:17:48.00,SoraDefault,,0000,0000,0000,,Even I'm... Um...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:48.00,0:17:49.44,SoraDefault,,0000,0000,0000,,Um?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:51.02,0:17:54.13,SoraDefault,,0000,0000,0000,,It doesn't matter! Just don't try to shoulder it all yourself!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:54.13,0:17:56.38,SoraDefault,,0000,0000,0000,,Even I can listen to what you have to say!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:57.09,0:17:59.00,SoraDefault,,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you, Rio.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:59.00,0:18:01.71,SoraDefault,,0000,0000,0000,,Then I'll take your offer and tell you.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.71,0:18:03.05,SoraDefault,,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:03.05,0:18:04.42,SoraDefault,,0000,0000,0000,,Actually...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:06.24,0:18:09.82,SoraDefault,,0000,0000,0000,,I've put on some weight this summer!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:09.82,0:18:10.40,SoraDefault,,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:10.40,0:18:13.90,SoraDefault,,0000,0000,0000,,If I don't lose it, I might not fit into my winter uniform.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:14.46,0:18:18.99,SoraDefault,,0000,0000,0000,,I heard that if you only eat watermelon for a while, you can lose weight, so I thought I would try it.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:18.99,0:18:21.54,SoraDefault,,0000,0000,0000,,What's wrong, Rio?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.61,0:18:26.04,SoraDefault,,0000,0000,0000,,Will you stop playing dumb?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:26.04,0:18:29.02,SoraDefault,,0000,0000,0000,,You were in the front lines at the battle at Binnenland and-
Dialogue: 0,0:18:29.02,0:18:30.75,SoraDefault,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:30.75,0:18:34.49,SoraDefault,,0000,0000,0000,,So you thought I was remembering that?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:34.78,0:18:37.80,SoraDefault,,0000,0000,0000,,Y- You weren't?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:42.94,0:18:44.74,SoraDefault,,0000,0000,0000,,It's so pretty.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.74,0:18:47.20,SoraDefault,,0000,0000,0000,,Should we head down too?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:02.94,0:19:05.02,SoraDefault,,0000,0000,0000,,So you made one too, Kureha?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:05.02,0:19:08.59,SoraDefault,,0000,0000,0000,,It's not like I believe in souls or anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:08.59,0:19:10.34,SoraDefault,,0000,0000,0000,,It's part of my duties.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:10.34,0:19:11.70,SoraDefault,,0000,0000,0000,,Excuse me...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:11.70,0:19:14.17,SoraDefault,,0000,0000,0000,,Who are you sending, Filicia?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:15.39,0:19:17.97,SoraDefault,,0000,0000,0000,,My old friends,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:17.97,0:19:21.18,SoraDefault,,0000,0000,0000,,and a soldier whose name I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:21.18,0:19:25.31,SoraDefault,,0000,0000,0000,,The ones who helped me realize the most important thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:25.31,0:19:27.90,SoraDefault,,0000,0000,0000,,Are those the people...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:27.90,0:19:30.05,SoraDefault,,0000,0000,0000,,Filicia...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:30.05,0:19:33.54,SoraDefault,,0000,0000,0000,,If you're worried about anything, I...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.54,0:19:37.04,SoraDefault,,0000,0000,0000,,I might not be able to help, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:37.04,0:19:39.20,SoraDefault,,0000,0000,0000,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:40.03,0:19:42.98,SoraDefault,,0000,0000,0000,,It looks like I made you worry about me.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.98,0:19:45.14,SoraDefault,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:45.14,0:19:46.89,SoraDefault,,0000,0000,0000,,But I'm okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:46.89,0:19:48.85,SoraDefault,,0000,0000,0000,,You're making me sad.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:49.46,0:19:52.24,SoraDefault,,0000,0000,0000,,I want to worry about you!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.24,0:19:55.67,SoraDefault,,0000,0000,0000,,The way you always worry about me, Filicia!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:55.67,0:19:59.29,SoraDefault,,0000,0000,0000,,Because I make you worry.\N I want to worry about you!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:59.29,0:20:03.98,SoraDefault,,0000,0000,0000,,Because I love you, Filicia!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:06.80,0:20:10.06,SoraDefault,,0000,0000,0000,,I love you too, Kanata.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:10.85,0:20:13.76,SoraDefault,,0000,0000,0000,,Always stay the way you are now.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:13.76,0:20:15.12,SoraDefault,,0000,0000,0000,,Please.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:16.18,0:20:17.60,SoraDefault,,0000,0000,0000,,Filicia...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:17.60,0:20:20.80,SoraDefault,,0000,0000,0000,,You're always trying to tell me
Dialogue: 0,0:20:20.80,0:20:24.32,SoraDefault,,0000,0000,0000,,not to fear putting my feelings into words.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:25.15,0:20:28.78,SoraDefault,,0000,0000,0000,,I think it's a wonderful thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:32.05,0:20:33.98,SoraDefault,,0000,0000,0000,,Commander...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:36.40,0:20:38.25,SoraDefault,,0000,0000,0000,,Filicia...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:38.25,0:20:40.17,SoraDefault,,0000,0000,0000,,Me too...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:44.93,0:20:47.16,SoraDefault,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, you three...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:47.16,0:20:49.43,SoraDefault,,0000,0000,0000,,I love you all...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:59.19,0:21:02.70,SoraDefault,,0000,0000,0000,,Until next year then, ancestors.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:07.97,0:21:11.20,SoraDefault,,0000,0000,0000,,Dad. Mom.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:21.92,0:21:23.58,SoraDefault,,0000,0000,0000,,Mother.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:23.58,0:21:24.72,SoraDefault,,0000,0000,0000,,Sister.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:25.51,0:21:27.60,SoraDefault,,0000,0000,0000,,That girl...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:31.69,0:21:37.23,SoraDefault,,0000,0000,0000,,Rio, you were just asking if there were any meaning in this world, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:37.23,0:21:39.04,SoraDefault,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:39.04,0:21:43.80,SoraDefault,,0000,0000,0000,,Ever since I survived the battle alone, I've pondered the same question.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:44.84,0:21:47.37,SoraDefault,,0000,0000,0000,,Why did I, alone, survive?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:47.37,0:21:51.12,SoraDefault,,0000,0000,0000,,Was there any meaning in it?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:47.37,0:21:51.12,SoraDefault,,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}Listen up. You can't just space out like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:51.12,0:21:53.23,SoraDefault,,0000,0000,0000,,And then I realized.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:53.99,0:21:57.88,SoraDefault,,0000,0000,0000,,There can't possibly be any meaning in this world.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:00.27,0:22:02.13,SoraDefault,,0000,0000,0000,,But isn't that wonderful in its own right?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:04.41,0:22:08.60,SoraDefault,,0000,0000,0000,,Because if there isn't any, we can find our own.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:11.78,0:22:15.46,SoraDefault,,0000,0000,0000,,And I found mine.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:15.46,0:22:17.86,SoraDefault,,0000,0000,0000,,My meaning in being alive.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:18.90,0:22:21.50,SoraDefault,,0000,0000,0000,,And so even the priest joined in!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:21.50,0:22:22.85,SoraDefault,,0000,0000,0000,,And then? And then?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:22.85,0:22:25.66,SoraDefault,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, he was really bad at it, so Sister Yumina...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:27.50,0:22:33.31,SoraDefault,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't want them to suffer the way I did.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:33.98,0:22:35.52,SoraDefault,,0000,0000,0000,,Neither do I.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:10.67,0:24:14.47,SoraDefault,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(100,100)\pos(960,405)\c&H020202&\bord0}Next time: Telephone Duty - Declare a State of Emergency
